# Enterprise Workflow

```text
Invoice Image
        ↓
Azure Content Understanding
        ↓
Structured JSON Extraction
        ↓
Azure AI Foundry Agent
        ↓
Invoice Fraud Detection
        ↓
REAL / FAKE Classification
```



# AI Invoice Fraud Detection Agent Setup Guide

## 1. Install Required Libraries

Run the following command:

```bash
pip install azure-ai-projects>=2.1.0
pip install azure-identity
```

---

## 2. Login to Azure

Authenticate using Azure CLI:

```bash
az login
```

A browser login page will appear.

Complete authentication using your Azure account.

---

## 3. Verify Azure Subscription

After login:

```bash
az account show
```

---

## 4. Configure Azure AI Foundry Project

Update the following variables in your Python code:

```python
endpoint = "YOUR_AZURE_AI_FOUNDRY_ENDPOINT"

my_agent = "ai-detection-invoice"

my_version = "8"
```

---

## 5. Upload Invoice Image

Place your invoice image in the project folder:

```text
invoice.jpg
```

Supported formats:

* JPG
* PNG
* PDF

---

## 6. Run AI Invoice Detection Agent

Execute the Python script:

```bash
python app.py
```

---

## 7. AI Agent Features

The AI agent can:

* Analyze uploaded invoice images
* Detect fake or suspicious invoices
* Compare invoice patterns
* Identify anomalies
* Explain fraud indicators

---

## 8. Example Output

```text
This invoice is likely FAKE because the invoice structure differs from known invoice patterns and the total amount appears suspicious.
```

